I wanna go back to Aristotle.

01:05:17.145 --> 01:05:21.440
Okay, this was during Aristotle's lifetime

01:05:21.440 --> 01:05:23.660
but I do not that he was involved.

01:05:23.660 --> 01:05:25.250
But, the dates right, right.

01:05:25.250 --> 01:05:26.960
So, there's a mission to set up a colony

01:05:26.960 --> 01:05:29.763
in the Adriatic because
of the Etruscan pirates.

01:05:31.060 --> 01:05:34.330
And the ships had to be
recruited from private lives.

01:05:34.330 --> 01:05:36.240
The ships were owned and the crews,

01:05:36.240 --> 01:05:37.280
it's a huge operation.

01:05:37.280 --> 01:05:39.760
There was like, 200 ships
and horses and soldiers,

01:05:39.760 --> 01:05:41.120
and sailors and so on.

01:05:41.120 --> 01:05:46.120
And, the people who were wealthy

01:05:46.340 --> 01:05:50.060
were appointed to deliver
a fully equipped ship

01:05:50.060 --> 01:05:51.653
to the port Piraeus.

01:05:53.470 --> 01:05:54.950
Fairness was assured.

01:05:54.950 --> 01:05:56.500
Now this is amazing.

01:05:56.500 --> 01:05:58.640
What the council said is,

01:05:58.640 --> 01:06:02.360
okay, these things are called
liturgies, I'm not sure why.

01:06:02.360 --> 01:06:04.200
Hundreds of them were
given out to wealthy people

01:06:04.200 --> 01:06:05.630
and said, you have to produce this ship

01:06:05.630 --> 01:06:06.980
you have to do that.

01:06:06.980 --> 01:06:08.900
Now here's how fairness was ensured.

01:06:08.900 --> 01:06:09.733
Brilliant.

01:06:11.000 --> 01:06:15.283
The liturgy was allocated
in the following way.

01:06:18.056 --> 01:06:20.380
Suppose I got a liturgy.

01:06:20.380 --> 01:06:22.630
But, I happen to know that Micheal

01:06:22.630 --> 01:06:25.330
who didn't get a liturgy
was wealthier than me.

01:06:25.330 --> 01:06:28.380
I go to Micheal and I say,
"Micheal take my liturgy."

01:06:28.380 --> 01:06:30.950
And if he refuses then his alternative

01:06:30.950 --> 01:06:32.723
is we exchange our wealth.

01:06:34.340 --> 01:06:35.900
Got it?

01:06:35.900 --> 01:06:37.380
I'm a citizen.

01:06:37.380 --> 01:06:39.370
The citizen's council
doesn't how wealthy he is,

01:06:39.370 --> 01:06:40.810
they just thought I was wealthier.

01:06:40.810 --> 01:06:42.350
But I know, I'm his neighbor.

01:06:42.350 --> 01:06:44.140
I know how many cows he has, or whatever.

01:06:44.140 --> 01:06:46.570
So I go and I say, you take my liturgy

01:06:46.570 --> 01:06:47.713
or I take your cows.

01:06:48.780 --> 01:06:52.340
That's mechanism design at its best.

01:06:52.340 --> 01:06:54.280
Because it's using private information

01:06:54.280 --> 01:06:56.270
the fact that I know
he's wealthier than me

01:06:56.270 --> 01:06:59.170
to essentially allocate
the burdens of this thing.

01:06:59.170 --> 01:07:02.542
So, this was a set of
incentives which were fair.

01:07:02.542 --> 01:07:05.080
The incentives were given as prices.

01:07:05.080 --> 01:07:06.940
They were not set as
incentives, for example,

01:07:06.940 --> 01:07:08.920
the herald of the council of 500

01:07:08.920 --> 01:07:12.320
is to announce the crowns at
the contest, the festival,

01:07:12.320 --> 01:07:14.360
in the order that the competitive zeal

01:07:14.360 --> 01:07:16.660
of the trierachs, that is
the captains of these ships,

01:07:16.660 --> 01:07:18.940
towards the demos would
be evident, and so on.

01:07:18.940 --> 01:07:20.973
A clear public purpose was stated.

01:07:21.980 --> 01:07:25.293
Substantial fines for those
who didn't do it were imposed.

