01:19:11.410 --> 01:19:13.630
in a public goods game
it has a big effect.

01:19:13.630 --> 01:19:15.440
And by the way that effect takes place

01:19:15.440 --> 01:19:18.610
even if we introduce what's called

01:19:18.610 --> 01:19:20.000
the perfect stranger treatment,

01:19:20.000 --> 01:19:23.320
which means every round
the groups are shuffled.

01:19:23.320 --> 01:19:25.160
So, if we're in a group together now,

01:19:25.160 --> 01:19:26.820
and I don't contribute and you punish me,

01:19:26.820 --> 01:19:29.220
you couldn't possibly be doing that

01:19:29.220 --> 01:19:32.120
in order to, that I would
shape up to your benefit.

01:19:32.120 --> 01:19:34.226
'Cause you know I'll
be somewhere else next.

01:19:34.226 --> 01:19:37.150
And, the other thing which we notice is

01:19:37.150 --> 01:19:39.190
being punished by a peer

01:19:39.190 --> 01:19:43.230
who apparently has no
selfish reason for doing that

01:19:43.230 --> 01:19:44.520
has a big impact.

01:19:44.520 --> 01:19:46.490
That is, it's not the punishment.

01:19:46.490 --> 01:19:49.890
For example, in these
games a verbal admonition

01:19:50.840 --> 01:19:55.130
